%N A156035 Decimal expansion of 3 + 2*sqrt(2).
%C A156035 Limit_{n -> oo} b(n+1)/b(n) = 3+2*sqrt(2) for b = A155464, A155465, A155466.
%C A156035 Limit_{n -> oo} b(n)/b(n-1) = 3+2*sqrt(2) for b = A001652, A001653, A002315, A156156, A156157, A156158. - _Klaus Brockhaus_, Sep 23 2009
%C A156035 From _Richard R. Forberg_, Aug 14 2013: (Start)
%C A156035 Ratios b(n+1)/b(n) for all sequences of the form b(n) = 6*b(n-1) - b(n-2), for any initial values of b(0) and b(1), converge to this ratio.
%C A156035 Ratios b(n+1)/b(n) for all sequences of the form b(n) = 5*b(n-1) + 5*b(n-2) + b(n-3), for all b(0), b(1) and b(2) also converge to 3 + 2*sqrt(2). For example see A084158 (Pell Triangles).
%C A156035 Ratios of alternating values, b(n+2)/b(n), for all sequences of the form b(n) = 2*b(n-1) + b(n-2), also converge to 3 + 2*sqrt(2). These include A000129 (Pell Numbers). Also see A014176. (End)
%C A156035 Let ABCD be a square inscribed in a circle. When P is the midpoint of the arc AB, then the ratio (PC*PD)/(PA*PB) is equal to 3+2*sqrt(2). See the Mathematical Reflections link. - _Michel Marcus_, Jan 10 2017
%C A156035 Limit of ratios of successive terms of A001652 when n-> infinity. - _Harvey P. Dale_, Jun 16 2017; improved by _Bernard Schott_, Feb 28 2022
%C A156035 A quadratic integer with minimal polynomial x^2 - 6x + 1. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jul 11 2020
%C A156035 Ratio between radii of the large circumscribed circle R and the small internal circle r drawn on the Sangaku tablet at Isaniwa Jinjya shrine in Ehime Prefecture (pictures in links). - _Bernard Schott_, Feb 25 2022
%C A156035 Equals r(6) where r(x)=sqrt(r(x^2-2)) as iteration count -> oo (true for all x >= 2: r(x) + 1/r(x) = x). Related: r(3)=A104457, r(4)=A019973, r(5)=A107905, r(7)=A374883. - _Charles L. Hohn_, Dec 16 2025
